<paragraph id="8BB7368AD850FFDF3CB4FDAA300AF91B" blockId="5.[151,1059,527,637]" pageId="5" pageNumber="964">
D i a g n o s i s: The genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C084D09D850FFDF3DF7FDB5306DF942" authorityName="Kirsch" authorityYear="1871" box="[468,594,527,548]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Aphelocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="966" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97CEA98D850FFDF3DF7FDB5306DF942" box="[468,594,527,548]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="964">Aphelocerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
KIRSCH was revised in 2005 (OPITZ 2005). This work included a key to species. 
<emphasis id="B97CEA98D850FFDF3E1CFD973137F924" box="[575,776,557,578]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="964">
<taxonomicName id="4C084D09D850FFDF3E1CFD973081F924" authorityName="Kirsch" authorityYear="1871" box="[575,702,557,578]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Aphelocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="966" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Aphelocerus</taxonomicName>
nodus
</emphasis>
specimens key out to 
<emphasis id="B97CEA98D850FFDF382FFD973331F939" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="964">A. formicoides</emphasis>
OPITZ from which 
<emphasis id="B97CEA98D850FFDF3DC6FDF0307EF939" box="[485,577,586,607]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="964">A. nodus</emphasis>
specimens differ by showing a more oblong pronotum and broader phallobasic lobes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB7368AD850FFDF3CB4FD37317DF8EA" blockId="5.[151,1059,652,909]" pageId="5" pageNumber="964">
D e s c r i p t i o n: Size: Length 
<quantity id="4CF09B6FD850FFDF3E27FD36306AF9C4" box="[516,597,652,674]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" pageId="5" pageNumber="964" unit="mm" value="4.5">4.5 mm</quantity>
; width 
<quantity id="4CF09B6FD850FFDF3E82FD3730CEF9C4" box="[673,753,653,674]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" pageId="5" pageNumber="964" unit="mm" value="2.3">2.3 mm</quantity>
. Form: As in 
<figureCitation id="13332A0FD850FFDF3F5CFD3731E8F9C4" box="[895,983,652,675]" captionStart="Figs 262-265" captionStartId="93.[151,191,1499,1521]" captionTargetBox="[153,1060,199,1483]" captionTargetId="figure@93.[153,1061,199,1485]" captionTargetPageId="93" captionText="Figs 262-265: Habitus; (262) Aphelocerus copanus; (263) A. ligulus; (264) A. magnipannus; (265) A. nodus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746792" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746792/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="964">Fig. 265</figureCitation>
. Color: Black; row of white setae on metepisternum. Head: Genae and epicranium extended; gena wrinkled behind eyes; interocular depression and frontal umbo shallow; antenna (
<figureCitation id="13332A0FD850FFDF3CBCFD5F32DDF99D" box="[159,226,741,763]" captionStart="Figs 1-27" captionStartId="70.[151,191,1302,1324]" captionTargetBox="[155,1057,207,1268]" captionTargetId="figure@70.[155,1058,207,1283]" captionTargetPageId="70" captionText="Figs 1-27: Antennae; (1) Aphelocerus nodus; (2) A. copanus; (3) A. magnipannus; (4) A. yoro; (5) A. sparicapillus; (6) A. tigra. (7) A. nolus; (8) A. ligulus; (9) Perilypus schusteri; (10) P. apunctus; (11) P. virgulatus; (12) P. izabal; (13) P. alpinus; (14) Cregya fuscomacula; (15) Phonius versus; (16) Pujoliclerus ariquemes; (17) Pelonium falcatum; (18) Pujoliclerus cnecostus; (19) P. trunculus. (20) P. sentus; (21) P. testudinatus; (22) P. catie; (23) P. flavidus; (24) P. convexus; (25) P. meloinus; (26) P. mexicoensis; (27) P. tuxtlas." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746746" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746746/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="964">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
) capitate, funicular antennomeres filiform, progressively shorter and wider towards capitulum, capitulum not compact; eyes finely facetted, eye narrower than frons (EW/FW 18/40). Thorax: Pronotum (
<figureCitation id="13332A0FD850FFDF3E14FCA530A8F853" box="[567,663,799,821]" captionStart="Figs 179-193" captionStartId="81.[151,191,1359,1381]" captionTargetBox="[167,1032,201,1342]" captionTargetId="figure@81.[152,1058,201,1346]" captionTargetPageId="81" captionText="Figs 179-193: Pronota; 179) Phonius versus; (180) Perilypus arsus; (181) A. nodus; (182) Pyticara frontegalba; (183) Pelonium implacide; (184) Neorthoplera quintana; (185) Perilypus virgulatus; (186) P. alpinus; (187) Amboakis expandosa; (188) Ampleris jatai; (189) Megaphloeus jasuni; (190) Amboakis bermejo (191) Madoniella delta; (192) Megaphloeus imparilus; (193) Pyticeroides brevitubulus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746768" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746768/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="964">Fig. 181</figureCitation>
) sub-globose, very finely punctate; (PW/PL 75/95); elytra short and boldly convex, with shallow longitudinal carina behind basal tumescence, disc with striae of very small setiferous punctures (EL/EW 165/70). Abdomen: Pygidium transverse 
<emphasis id="B97CEA98D850FFDF3DFBFCCD33E0F8EB" bold="true" box="[472,479,887,909]" pageId="5" pageNumber="964">/</emphasis>
scutiform; aedeagus as in 
<figureCitation id="13332A0FD850FFDF3EC5FCCD317DF8EA" box="[742,834,887,909]" captionStart="Figs 201-206" captionStartId="83.[151,191,1264,1286]" captionTargetBox="[153,1059,191,1248]" captionTargetId="figure@83.[153,1059,191,1248]" captionTargetPageId="83" captionText="Figs 201-206: Aedeagi; (201) Aphelocerus copanus; (202) A. ligulus; (203) A. magnipannus; (204) A. nodus; (205) A. nolus; (206) A. sparicapillus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746772" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746772/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="964">Fig. 204.</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
