<paragraph id="8BB7368AD850FFDF3CB4FBBF30E1FF5E" blockId="5.[151,1058,1029,1080]" pageId="5" pageNumber="964">
E t y m o l o g y: The trivial name, 
<emphasis id="B97CEA98D850FFDF3E09FBBF3058FF7C" box="[554,615,1029,1050]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="964">nodus</emphasis>
, is a Latin adjective meaning &quot;swelling&quot;; with reference to the tumescence at the base of the elytra.
